@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Shared Delete Sequence
hide footbox
skinparam sequence {
  actorBorderColor #0f172a
  actorBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  participantBorderColor #0f172a
  participantBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  participantFontColor #0f172a
  lifeLineBorderColor #94a3b8
  groupBorderColor #cbd5e1
  groupBackgroundColor #f8fafc
}
participant BaseReconciler
participant "OSOKServiceManager" as ServiceManager
participant OCI
participant "Kubernetes Secret" as SecretStore
note over BaseReconciler,ServiceManager
Finalizer discipline, delete status persistence,
work requests, and optional Secret cleanup
end note
group Step 1
BaseReconciler -> ServiceManager: Handle delete request with finalizer discipline
note right of ServiceManager
Keep the OSOK finalizer until delete
confirmation or an explicit not-supported
policy says otherwise.
end note
end
group Step 2
ServiceManager -> OCI: Delete target resource
loop confirmation until terminal delete state
ServiceManager -> OCI: GET or list fallback
end
note right of OCI
When delete stays pending or returns an error,
BaseReconciler persists service-manager status
mutations before the next reconcile loop.
end note
end
group Step 3
opt repo-authored secret cleanup
ServiceManager -> SecretStore: Delete ready-only secret when policy allows
end
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: Remove finalizer when delete is confirmed
note right of SecretStore
Controller-local specialization supplies
delete confirmation via GET, datasource list
fallback, or provider wait helpers.
end note
end
@enduml
